SIMPLE: bewilder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bewilder
<hw>Be*wil"der</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Bewildered</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Bewildering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>be-</ets> + <ets>wilder</ets>.]</ety> <def>To lead into perplexity
or confusion, as for lack of a plain path; to perplex with mazes; or in
general, to perplex or confuse greatly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lost and <qex>bewildered</qex> in the fruitless search.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To perplex; puzzle; entangle; confuse; confound;
mystify; embarrass; lead astray.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bewildered</ent>⟦br⟧
